fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.resource

Class PersistentResourceDecorator

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.resource.PersistentResourceDecorator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PersistentResource, Closeable, AutoCloseable, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.resource.Resource, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.resource.Resource.Internal

    public class PersistentResourceDecorator
extends Object
implements PersistentResource
    An empty PersistentResource decorator that delegates all method calls to the decorated resource.

    This class can be extended by external tools to add behavior to an existing PersistentResource.

      • getAllInstances

        public org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject> getAllInstances(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EClass eClass)
        Description copied from interface: PersistentResource
        Computes the set of instances of the given EClass (including its sub-types).

        This method is similar to PersistentResource.getAllInstances(EClass, boolean) with strict=false.

        Specified by:
        getAllInstances in interface PersistentResource
        Parameters:
        eClass - the EClass for which look for instances
        Returns:
        all the instances of the given EClass from the resource

      • getAllInstances

        public org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject> getAllInstances(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EClass eClass,
                                                                                        boolean strict)
        Description copied from interface: PersistentResource
        Computes the set of instances of the given EClass.
        Specified by:
        getAllInstances in interface PersistentResource
        Parameters:
        eClass - the EClass for which look for instances
        strict - true if the lookup searches for strict instances
        Returns:
        if true then the method returns only the strict instances of the given EClass, otherwise it also returns the instances of the sub-types of eClass.
